Sentencas: In this paper, four types of doped ceria powders and sinters, including Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95, Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9, Sm0.1Ce0.9O1.95 and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9, are prepared and characterized.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The results indicate that the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 samples possess the lowest densification temperature and a relatively optimal conductivity, which make it more suitable for use as an interlayer compared to other doped ceria.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: In addition, a series of interlayers were prepared from Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 powders with different precalcination temperatures using an industrial screen printing method.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The area-specific resistances of these interlayers were determined from their microstructures, including the grain and pore size, electrolyte/interlayer interface, layer uniformity and density, which are significantly dependent on the precalcination temperatures of the powders.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: A minimum area-specific resistance of 0.036 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C was obtained for the sample with Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 powders precalcined at 950 degrees C (the corresponding BET value was approximately 20 m(2) g(-1)).
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: In addition, lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cells were prepared with the as-prepared Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 interlayer.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Their power density was measured and determined to be 0.72 W cm(-2) at 750 degrees C (0.75 V, active area of 64 cm(2)).
Titulo: Synthesis and electrical properties of screen-printed doped ceria interlayer for IT-SOFC applications
